The paper discusses policy search methods for continuous control tasks, which are typically studied in the fields of machine learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses sample efficiency properties, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
